Great War Dundee

This is Dundee's story of those that served in the First World War, and of the people left at home

More about John Macdonald

Dundee People’s Journal 16th November 1918

Macdonald—Died of wounds, at casualty clearing station, France, on 16th October 1918, Sapper John Macdonald R.E., third son of Mr and Mrs Macdonald, 17 Lawrence Street, Dundee.
